"Abstract The plastic money card offers benefits to consumers, bankers and retailers alike. But as well as being convenient to use of, platic cards can be easy to lose, steal and, in some cases, duplicate while cash dispensers, automated teller machines and point-of-sale sale terminals can break down or make mistakes. A recent OECD report1 claims that the consumer is often poorly protected from the cosenquences of such such incidents, especially as the banks themselves lay down the rules and establish (and modify) the conditions of use for the cards they issue."
